node.title: Teen arrested in connection with Baltimore shooting that killed 2, injured 28
node.description: Detectives believe the teen was involved in a mass shooting Sunday in South Baltimore that left two people dead and 28 injured.
node.content: ["Baltimore police arrested a 17-year-old male on Friday morning in connection with a\u00a0mass shooting\u00a0Sunday in South Baltimore that left two people dead and 28 injured, authorities said in a news statement. Members of the homicide and SWAT teams arrested the suspect at 7:00 a.m., police said.\u00a0", "The teenager is being charged with possession of a firearm by a minor, and reckless endangerment among other charges.", "This is a breaking news story. Please check back for developments.", "Cara Tabachnick is a news editor for CBSNews.com. Contact her at cara.tabachnick@cbsinteractive.com"]
